Business Case: As an external system user, I want to set the value to  dataSync  flag for the list of Purchase Orders. Acceptance Criteria: There should be a new API that allows users to update the  dataSync  flag value The type of the API should be  POST . The user should be able to change the  dataSync  flag for the purchase orders in bulk The API should adhere to the API Payload size standards. the model of this API should be externallySynced  (Required) The boolean value should be given The validation error should be thrown if no value or invalid value is specified. Purchase Order Reference  (Required) The precedence should be: ID External ID Doc No. This object should be of Array type. It should accept a list of Purchase Orders that need to be updated. The validation error should be thrown if no value or invalid value is specified. Documentation: There should be a new entry in the API Documentation in the  Purchase Orders  sub-menu of the  Transactional APIs  menu This entry should be for the following APIs: Purchase Order  externallySynced  ( please use the naming convention as per standards ) The API summary( which appears next to the API endpoint)  should read ‘ Update the Purchase Order externallySynced   flag’ . The details should be ' Update the Purchase Order externallySynced   flag '. In the API documentation, the parameter  externallySynced  details should read ' A flag indicating whether the data is synchronized with the external system. '  Technical Details: URL: POST  /purchase-orders/sync-status Request Model: {
  externallySynced : true,
  purchaseOrderRefs : [
    {
      "id" : null,
      "externalId" : null,
      "docNo" : "9000010001"
      "type" : "PurchaseOrderModel"
    }
  ]
} Validations: If the give references are invalid, we give validation errors, e.g Purchase order 00000001 not found. Response: Purchase orders successfully synced with the external system. Q&A:

